    "title": "[Since Gazprom was making exorbitant profits and Aniruddha Roy was identified as...",
    "description": "[Since Gazprom was making exorbitant profits and Aniruddha Roy was identified as close to Justice S. K. Sinha, there was no longer any point in keeping him as Gazprom's local agent. Gazprom's new local agent became an institution named National Electronic BD. The owners of this institution are a Russian citizen, Mia Sattar, and his brother Sohail. National Electronic BD, besides Gazprom, also obtained the local agency for Russia's food-exporting institution, Prodintorg. That was around mid-2022. Immediately afterward, National Electronic BD secured two major deals. One of them was a purchase order for Prodintorg to buy 500,000 tonnes of wheat from Russia at an inflated price \u2013 about 240 crore taka above the market price. The Energy Division is spending 694 crore taka to have Gazprom drill three gas wells in Bhola. However, through the state-owned institution Bapex, the cost of drilling each well is 80 crore taka. Thus, the total expected cost would have been 240 crore taka. By using Gazprom, the additional expenditure is 454 crore taka. Investigations have shown that the reason for the government's additional expenditure of 694 crore taka on wheat imports and gas well drilling is the cost of the Russian company's local agent or intermediary. That intermediary in Bangladesh is Md. Sohail. He has an institution named National Electronic BD in Mohakhali, Dhaka. Making National Electronic BD the local agent for Gazprom and Prodintorg was primarily due to the influence of Bangladesh's ambassador to Russia, Dr. S. M. Saiful Hoque. Using the flag-bearing car of the Bangladesh Embassy in Russia, Saiful Hoque introduced Mia Sattar to Russian businessmen. Under Saiful Hoque's sole authority, he did not stop at merely securing the local agency for these two institutions; during the Awami League's final term, he secured two projects worth 694 crore taka without market competition. At that time, whenever Saiful Hoque came to Dhaka, even his hotel rent was paid by National Electronic BD. Nothing happened to Saiful Hoque. He, along with his Indian wife, is living quite comfortably in his own five-story house in Mumbai's most expensive Juhu Beach area. And Dr. Abul Barkat is serving time in jail. So why all this discussion about Saiful Hoque? It is to show that most of those who cause Bangladesh's total ruin are not even known to many people. Moreover, they never face justice. My assumption is that National Electronic BD's owner Sohail and his brother Mia Sattar are still doing business comfortably in Bangladesh. Because they had written on their website that they were also the local agents for the Rooppur Nuclear Power Plant \u2013 and that is why all this discussion exists. Although this is no longer written on their website.] Read the full piece by Arifuzzaman Tuhin (check comment below).",
    "link": "https://www.facebook.com/saerzulkarnain/posts/pfbid02YRbqex5VbccqvR4FohzKZuj3587nyVK7v1AZCNZMo3CAy2cedMSht1qidc9oaGmBl",
    "guid": "https://www.facebook.com/saerzulkarnain/posts/pfbid02YRbqex5VbccqvR4FohzKZuj3587nyVK7v1AZCNZMo3CAy2cedMSht1qidc9oaGmBl",
